First, we need to find the symmetric difference (A △ B). The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets A or B, but not in their intersection.

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3} (union of A and B)
A ∩ B = {2} (intersection of A and B)

A △ B = {1, 2, 3} - {2} = {1, 3}

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of (A △ B) × {1} and {1} × (A △ B).

(A △ B) × {1} = {(1, 1), (3, 1)}

{1} × (A △ B) = {(1, 1), (1, 3)}

So, (A △ B) × {1} = {(1, 1), (3, 1)} and {1} × (A △ B) = {(1, 1), (1, 3)}.
